<br>
For the long term damage output of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with an appropriate <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on a raid or in a group, the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should do <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>no more</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> damage than a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Monk</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>more</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> than that <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>directly</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> dealt <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bard</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> who is spending most of his effort in support.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Damage Shields</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are considered utility for the sake of this discussion, as they enable <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>others</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to do damage.  Likewise, most <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bard</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> support songs are excluded as well.<br>
<br>
My reasoning is as follows: <br>
<br>
After sufficient support, only additional damage dealers are required on raids.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> therefore should be decent damage dealers, but no better than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Monks</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
In groups and on raids, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Value ~= Damage + Utility</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> clearly provide less utility to a group or raid than a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bard</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Therefore, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should deal more damage than a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bard</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does directly.<br>
<br>
I am more concerned with establishing whether these are reasonable bounds than determining exactly where we stand within those bounds.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
ArchMage, Ancient Fellowship, Xev<br>
