<br>
We know the fight lasted 4 minutes and 45 seconds or 285 seconds.   With Boots of Bladecalling...the Epic Pet Mage in this fight could have nuked 15 times for 600dmg each ( no resists ).  For a grand total of 9000 Nuke Dmg for zero mana.<br>
<br>
9000 + 6071 = 15071<br>
<br>
The mage in this senerio did more damage then the AVERAGED Monks and just a little less then the AVERAGED Rogues.  IF the mage lacked the Boots, they could have used mana and Shock of Fiery Blades to achieve 9000-12000 ( again..no resists ) nuke damage.<br>
<br>
If you want to make a stab at resists...and go with horrible 50% resist rate..the Mage still would've clocked in at 10,500 damage for this fight...or just a hair under the AVERAGE Monks.<br>
<br>
I'd argue that in all situations where pets are allowed..the mage already meets and exceeds your proposed Monk mark for offensive damage.  I'm guessing that is what VI thinks too.<br>
<br>
The real trick is (1) Making pets 100% usable ( Indiff + /pet hold ) and (2) Convincing other players that the mage does do &quot;noticable&quot; damage with pets.<br>
