<br>
If you look at all of the things we summon, the only things that stand out as useful are Mod Rods and Pets.  CoTH is useful but for he most part is strickly for summoning late arivals.  Rogues have sneak/hide, evade, 70% bindwounds, considerably better ac/hps, and a larger amount of defensive skills and offensive disc.  I think when laying out a comparison forum; you must state how much weight you are giving certain skills and what are you comparing those skills to.<br>
<br>
How much weight should be given to rogue ac/hps when compared to the very small amount of hps that mages have.  <br>
Magician pets have a very low ac, that has to also be added to the mix. Sneak/Hide is one of the class defining abilities of the rogue class. No other class can use those two skills together to have the best invis in the game.  That is a very powerful ability and has to be compared to something of equal value to the mage.  <br>
<br>
I guess the point I am trying to make is comparing caster to melee is never really going to be a good idea when you are comparing damage.  A new weapon drop and a melee jumps further ahead in DPS.  Verant is never going to add new spells to allow casters to keep pace with item drops. Damage casters should ALWAYS IMHO out damage melee.  Wielding the very elements and throwing fire balls at your enemys should always be more damaging then a melee with a dirk.  The fact that conjuring hundreds of blades to strike our target is a weaker form of dealing damage then a rogue with a knife is the problem. With pet and dd a mage should out pace any other damage class in the game over time. When you look at our very weak list of utility it only seems fair. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=istaron>Istaron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#333333>(2/21/02 5:24:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Statue</span><hr size=1> The discussion here is about longterm damage over the course of a raid, not single mob encounters.<br>
