Which you did answer, I think:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Personally, I believe in the short term mages should out-damage monks by a great deal, and as the fight stretches monk damage should come closer to mage damage. But, I believe Magicians should always out-damage monks, and situationally out-damage rogues. I believe that in a long, drawn out fight, magicians should be right at monk damage.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The other thing I'm interested in is how much does player skill have to do with damage output from either of these classes?  Avoiding aggro is kind of like blackjak, do you hit and possibly bust?  Or do you play it conservatively and be content with an mediocre score in the hopes that it will be adequete?  How much work do monks and magicians have to do, respectively, to avoid gaining aggro to the detriment of the raid?<br>
<br>
Magician:<br>
<br>
Nuking speed, choice of nukes, pet placement, proximity...  anything else?<br>
<br>
Monk:<br>
<br>
Feign Death/Autoattack off, placement, proximity.. anything else?<br>
