<br>
However, now you also have to ask, where are you trying to balance?  The <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    whole</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> raid?  During the trash clearing, I just let the melee deal with it, and make mod rods for buffs, and for before the fight.  This is also when I summon most late comers, and make various other things (coldstones, arrows, etc).  If our nukes were faster, and our pets were safer, I still wouldn't use them during this part of the raid because I'd be doing utility.<br>
<br>
How about just the bosses then.  However, you again enter a &quot;which part are you balancing?&quot; area.  Kunark uber mobs have huge resists, low ac, and low hp.   They fall to melees real quick, but casters are pretty ineffective.  At the same time, these mobs are transition mobs and you will eventually leave them behind, so is it very important that they are perfectly balanced?  Velious uber mobs tend to have low resists, many hp, low ac.  This makes both melee and caster damage effective, in all the logs I've taken I come out to about 85% of a rogue damage (no DS) nearly every single time.  For me this is fine, I can happily play my mage doing this damage, and doing most of my utility on the way to the fight. I think it should be higher (like 90% or so), but 85% is fine.  Then you get to Luclin. The uber mobs here tend to have tons of hp, low resists, and really high AC.  This makes melees a lot less effective than they would be in Velious, while our spells land just as well as they did in Velious.  This has an effect on us too because it lowers pet output.  All the mobs from Luclin that I've logged have been changed since then, so I'd have to take more to find how much I do compared to rogues.  On a side note, I do not have a BWS or Boots of Bladecalling.<br>
<br>
Overall I find that my damage output is fine, even on long fights.  While I'd like it to be better, I'm not gonna worry about it too much till they finish, and itemize, the caster focus items (which they said they're still working on). <p>~~
